### Configuration Breakdown
* **`require_ci_to_pass: true`**: Codecov status checks will wait for all other CI checks (e.g. GitHub Actions tests) to pass before posting status checks to the PR.
* **`project.default.target: auto` / `threshold: 2%`**: The overall project coverage target is dynamic (automatically matches the coverage of the base commit) with a lenient `2%` threshold. This prevents build failures for minor coverage fluctuations.
* **`patch.default.target: 80%`**: Requires at least `80%` coverage on new or modified lines of code in pull requests.
* **`comment` customization**:
  * **`layout`**: Displays the reach, diff, flags, and files in the PR comment.
  * **`require_changes: true`**: Minimizes PR comment noise by only posting/updating comments when there is an actual change in coverage.

